---
description: Testing discipline before claiming something works
alwaysApply: true
---
- Never report a backend (Metal/CUDA/CPU) as working unless you actually ran
  it on that backend in this session. If you lack access to hardware for a
  backend, say so plainly and ask before claiming success.
- Every change to the KV cache, paged block table, scheduler, quantization,
  or sampling path needs a corresponding gate in `tests/` before it's
  considered done. The paged KV path in particular must stay bitwise-equal to
  the contiguous layout (the `--paged-cpu` / `--paged-metal` gates).
- When in doubt about correctness vs. speed, choose correctness first —
  this project's parent company builds for critical systems, so "probably
  right and fast" is not the bar.
